definitions.definition: A light fabric containing patterns of holes, usually built up from a single thread.
A cord or ribbon passed through eyelets in a shoe or garment , pulled tight and tied to fasten the shoe or garment firmly.
examples: your laces are untied, do them up!

definitions.definition: A snare or gin , especially one made of interwoven cords; a net .
Spirits added to coffee or another beverage .

main_definition: ( uncountable ) A light fabric containing patterns of holes, usually built up from a single thread.
